    <div class="wrapper">
      <div id="comments-15">
        
            <article id="comment-377">
              <time datetime="2010-09-25">September 25, 2010</time>
              <p>tanx 4 opening 1 in Old Street as it is a bit closer 2 me.  food from ur menus are really great,esp. thai calamari n that chilli prawn stir fry.......very fab, i always love the honey n ginger tea. most of the food on the list is fab. good work,keep it up n tanx</p>
              <p class="author">From Antwi</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-373">
              <time datetime="2010-09-25">September 25, 2010</time>
              <p>Busaba - one of my favourite London restaurants!
<br />Every single dish I had was delicious.</p>
              <p class="author">From Suzie</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-365">
              <time datetime="2010-09-24">September 24, 2010</time>
              <p>I love the food, the service is perfect and the atmosphere is great. 
<br />MY HUSBAND AND I LOVE BUSABA.</p>

<p>It's simply the best food ever.</p>
              <p class="author">From Adele La Belle</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-361">
              <time datetime="2010-09-24">September 24, 2010</time>
              <p>My husband &amp; I went to the Oxford location on Bird Street last night. Food was phenomenal - Sen Chan Pad Thai, Ginger Beef, Chinese Broccoli, Chicken Satay &amp; the most amazing Thai Calamari EVER! But special mention also has to go to Kevin (manager? server?) who was just totally awesome! Thanks for a GREAT dinner out all around! See you soon!</p>
              <p class="author">From Kristin</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-357">
              <time datetime="2010-09-24">September 24, 2010</time>
              <p>A gentleman on the street outside the underground suggested we go. Wowowow. Great food great price great calamari. Duck curry was outstanding. We came back the next night   Sorry to go home to miami we wont be happy with our Thai food anymore.</p>
              <p class="author">From S&j</p>
    
            </article>

